  %body{:xmlns => "http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"}
    %stuarttettdotcom-app#app{:detail => "logos"}
    %section#contentDetails.z1{:style => "display: none; visibility: hidden; min-height: 100vh;"}
      .progress-container.fade-in
        #progress-bar.progress-bar
      %figure.image.contain.fourSeventyTwo{"aria-label" => "", :role => "img", :style => "background-image: url(#{"/images/logo2.jpg"})"}
      .one-col
        %p Doppler's Dogpatch is a new premium ice cream brand in North Carolina.
        %p They wanted their brand to be centered around their dog, Doppler. They wanted a minimal and modern logo to be used on their pints and marketing materials.
      .one-col
        %p After some loose sketching, I decided to create a logo with a profile view. I created the dog head (and eventually the hat and ice cream scoop) entirely from circles.
      %figure.image.contain.fourSeventyTwo{"aria-label" => "", :role => "img", :style => "background-image: url(#{"/images/logo-doppler-circles.png"})"}
      %figure.image.contain.fourSeventyTwo{"aria-label" => "", :role => "img", :style => "background-image: url(#{"/images/logo-doppler-round1.png"})"}
      %div
        %p I played around with different ways of displaying the dog's profile.
        %p I decided to try adding a scoop of ice cream on the snout to better represent what the product is in a cute way.
      %div
        %p After iterating with the client a couple of times we ended up with a green and brown-gray color scheme. With a little splash of pink for the ice cream.
      %figure.image.contain.fourSeventyTwo{"aria-label" => "", :role => "img", :style => "background-image: url(#{"/images/logo1.jpg"})"}
      %figure.image.contain.fourSeventyTwo{"aria-label" => "", :role => "img", :style => "background-image: url(#{"/images/logo3.png"})"}
      .one-col
        %p BuildUp.tv is an online platform centered around the Maker/D.I.Y. community. I sketched several concepts, but this logo with the wood-cut ends stood out with it's simplicity and representation of the brand.
      .one-col
        %p SousChef is a mobile recipe app that I cofounded. I was inspired by the artwork from Lucky Peach magazine (R.I.P.), which is a little more rough and grungy than the current trends in mobile products. I wanted a bold color which stood out amongst apps on the iPhone's home screen and also didn't make the splash look like blood.
      %figure.image.contain.fourSeventyTwo{"aria-label" => "", :role => "img", :style => "background-image: url(#{"/images/logo4.png"})"}
